Fieldset
Real-time Definition: A container that groups related form elements together, creating a visual and semantic grouping. In real-world applications, it acts like a "section box" that organizes form fields into logical categories.

Real-time Use Cases:

Grouping personal information fields (name, email, phone)

Creating sections for address details

Organizing payment information

Separating emergency contact details

Grouping employment history fields

Legend
Real-time Definition: A caption or title for the fieldset that describes what the grouped elements represent. It acts as a "section header" that tells users what information they need to provide in that specific part of the form.

Real-time Use Cases:

"Personal Information" for name/contact details

"Employment Details" for job-related information

"Emergency Contact" for emergency information

"Bank Details" for payment information



----------------------------------------------Form ---------------------------------------------------------

